
Overview of verb petrify

The verb petrify has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (1) petrify -- (cause to become stonelike or stiff or dazed and stunned; "The horror petrified his feelings"; "Fear petrified her thinking")
2. lapidify, petrify -- (change into stone; "the wood petrified with time")
3. rigidify, ossify, petrify -- (make rigid and set into a conventional pattern; "rigidify the training schedule"; "ossified teaching methods"; "slogans petrify our thinking")
